title: ‘Kind of a Bop’: Watch Ariana Grande & Cynthia Erivo’s ‘Wicked’ Mini-Me’s Adorably Re-Create Viral ‘Elphaba, Glinda’ Song
summary: Which is which? Here's the sitch.
body: Ariana Grande and Cynthia Erivo ‘s musical Wicked explainer on The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon went viral last year — and now, there’s a version for the munchkins in your life too. Premiering exclusively on Billboard Family below, Karis Musongole and Scarlett Spears — who play young Elphaba and Glinda in the Wicked films, respectively — performed their own version of their older counterparts’ catchy jingle. “I’m a witch/ And I’m a witch/ But, which is which?/ Well, here’s the sitch,” they sing over a dance beat, alternating each line. title: These Black Friday Deals on Everything From JBL to Fenty Beauty are all Under $25 for a Limited Time
summary: 'Tis the season for saving.
body: All products and services featured are independently chosen by editors. However, Billboard may receive a commission on orders placed through its retail links, and the retailer may receive certain auditable data for accounting purposes. Black Friday is here at last, which means you can start checking off your gifting list without breaking the bank. ‘Tis the season to shop ’till you drop, and while there’s a bunch of savings opportunities for you to look through, the best deals, especially if you’re on a budget this year, are the under $25 items. Plenty of stores from Amazon to Nordstrom and even Ulta Beauty have a slew of under $25 options for shoppers to browse. While it’s certainly amazing to get an under $25 product, not all deals are created equal. With so many options, though, it’s hard to know what’s actually worth adding to cart. Not to fret, ShopBillboard is here to save the day. To streamline your shopping, we’ve compiled a few of our favorite products across categories like beauty, tech, music, fragrance and fashion, giving you our honest opinions on it all. title: Summer Walker Completes No. 1 Trilogy on Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums Chart
summary: Finally Over It follows its predecessors to a chart-topping result.
body: Summer Walker overcomes the competition on Billboard ’s Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums chart as her third full-length studio album, Finally Over It , starts atop the list dated Nov. 29. The album begins with 77,000 equivalent album units in the United States for the week of Nov. 14-20, according to Luminate, and is the highest total for any R&B album by a woman in 2025. Related Did the Wait Help or Hurt Summer Walker’s ‘Finally Over It’ First-Week Performance?
